result.execSummary:
Zebulion Oliver Magley was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Zebulion Oliver Magley was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:24 PM Court calls case.  Cites appearances.  Def is present, in custody.  Matthew J. Tingstad appears for the State.  Def provided PD info and complaint.  Court explains extradition hearing.  Def understands proceeding.  Court explains right to atty.  No questions.  Court summarizes complaint.  Warrant out of MI.  Court further explains process/Governor's warrant, etc.  Def understands.  Def admits who he is.  Court finds sufficient basis to hold def.  Court questions if def wants to waive extradition or fight extradition.  Def wants to waive extradition.  Understands advantage of atty.  Understands what he is waiving.  Def provided with waiver form.  Court reads questions to def.  Def checks boxes in court.  Def signs waiver.  Court signs its portion.  Waiver provided to clerk.  Adj.  1:33 p.m.  klr
